Package sg.dex.starfish

Interface Job<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of result returned by the Job
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MemoryJob, RemoteJob
    public interface Job<T>
    Interface representing a job executed via the Invoke API
    Version:
    0.5
    Author:
    Mike

    • Method Detail

      • getJobID

        String getJobID()
        Gets the Job ID associated with this Job. Job IDs are allocated by the agent implementation responsible for completing the job.
        Returns:
        jobID

      • isComplete

        boolean isComplete()
        Returns true if the Job has been completed. If the job is complete, the result may be obtained via getResult()
        Returns:
        boolean true if the job is complete, false otherwise.

      • getResult

        T getResult()
        Gets the result of the job as an Ocean asset
        Returns:
        The Asset resulting from the job, or null if not yet available
        Throws:
        AuthorizationException - if requestor does not have load permission
        StorageException - if unable to load the Asset
        JobFailedException - if the job failed during execution

      • awaitResult

        default T awaitResult()
        Waits for the result of the Operation and returns the result Asset WARNING: may never return if the job does not complete
        Returns:
        The Asset resulting from the job
        Throws:
        AuthorizationException - if requestor does not have load permission
        StorageException - if unable to load the Asset
        JobFailedException - if Job fails

      • awaitResult

        T awaitResult​(long timeoutMillis)
        Waits for the result of the Operation and returns the result Asset or returns null if the timeout in milliseconds expires before the asset is available. Implementations may throw these exceptions: throws TimeoutException if result is not available in timeoutMillis throws AuthorizationException if requestor does not have load permission throws StorageException if unable to load the Asset throws JobFailedException if Job fails
        Parameters:
        timeoutMillis - The number of milliseconds to wait for a result before returning null
        Returns:
        The Asset resulting from the job, or null if the timeout expires before the job completes
